## Shelf Tag Processing

Parse `Bookshelves` as comma-separated list; lowercase, strip whitespace.

### Step 1 — Classify each shelf tag

Each tag falls into one of these categories (processed in order):

| Category | Tags | Action |
|---|---|---|
| **Reading status** | `to-read`, `currently-reading`, `read`, `dnf-*` | → reading_status_id (see table below) |
| **DNF variant** | `dnf-permanent`, `dnf-read-later` | → reading_status DNF + add original tag to freeform tags |
| **Format (explicit)** | `library-hardback`, `library-hardcover`, `library-paper`, `library-kindle`, `library-kobo`, `library-audible` | → format_detail_id |
| **Format (explicit, Borrowed)** | `library-kindle-unlimited`, `library-overdrive` | → format_detail_id + ownership Borrowed + tag |
| **Format (Other, with tag)** | all other `library-*` | → Other Ebook or Other Audio + strip `library-` prefix + add remainder as freeform tag |
| **library-other** | `library-other` | → Other Ebook + add "other" as freeform tag |
| **Tag-only** | `freebie`, `stripped-or-arc` | → freeform tag; no format |
| **Non-Fiction indicator** | `biography`, `gaming`, `non-fiction`, `writing-and-movie-making` | → sets top_level_category_id = Non-Fiction; also processed for genre |
| **Genre tag** | see genre mapping section | → xref_book_item_genres; NOT added as freeform tag |
| **Unknown/other** | anything else | → freeform tag |

### Step 2 — Format detail mapping

| Shelf Tag | format_detail_id | ownership | tag added? |
|---|---|---|---|
| `library-hardback`, `library-hardcover` | 1 (Hardcover) | Owned | — |
| `library-paper` | 2 (Paperback) | Owned | — |
| `library-kindle` | 4 (Kindle) | Owned | — |
| `library-kobo` | 5 (Kobo) | Owned | — |
| `library-audible` | 7 (Audible) | Owned | — |
| `library-kindle-unlimited` | 4 (Kindle) | Borrowed | "kindle-unlimited" |
| `library-overdrive` | 6 (Other Ebook) | Borrowed | "overdrive" |
| `library-smashwords` | 6 (Other Ebook) | Owned | "smashwords" |
| `library-glose` | 6 (Other Ebook) | Owned | "glose" |
| `library-free-online` | 6 (Other Ebook) | Owned | "free-online" |
| `library-audio-file` | 8 (Other Audio) | Owned | "audio-file" |
| `library-audiocd` | 8 (Other Audio) | Owned | "audiocd" |
| `library-kobo-audio` | 8 (Other Audio) | Owned | "kobo-audio" |
| `library-chirp` | 8 (Other Audio) | Owned | "chirp" |
| `library-other` | 6 (Other Ebook) | Owned | "other" |
| Any other `library-*` | 6 (Other Ebook) | Owned | stripped name |

**Multi-format:** if a book has multiple format tags, create ONE `tbl_items` + `tbl_book_details` row, then one `tbl_book_copies` row per format.

**`freebie`, `stripped-or-arc`:** freeform tag only. No format, no ownership effect.

### Step 3 — Ownership status

Ownership is derived from library-* tags only. Reading status fields do not affect ownership.

| Condition | ownership_status_id |
|---|---|
| Has `library-*` tag(s) (excluding `library-kindle-unlimited`, `library-overdrive`) | Owned (id=1) |
| `library-kindle-unlimited` or `library-overdrive` only (no other Owned library-* tags) | Borrowed |
| `library-formerly-owned` | Formerly Owned (id=4) |
| No `library-*` tag, `exclusive_shelf = to-read` | Wanted (id=2) |
| No `library-*` tag, `exclusive_shelf = currently-reading` | Wanted (id=2) ← reclassified |
| No `library-*` tag, `exclusive_shelf = read` | Owned (id=1) ← flagged |
| Any other unresolvable combination | Pending ← flagged |

`ownership_status_id` is NOT NULL — every row must resolve to a value.

### Step 4 — Reading status

`Exclusive Shelf` field takes priority; `Bookshelves` used as fallback.

`currently-reading` is treated as stale data — all currently-reading books are reclassified as Want to Read.

| Value | reading_status_id |
|---|---|
| `read` | 1 (Read) |
| `currently-reading` | 3 (Want to Read) ← reclassified |
| `to-read` | 3 (Want to Read) |
| `dnf-permanent` or `dnf-read-later` (from Bookshelves) | 4 (DNF) + original tag added |

### Step 5 — top_level_category_id (Fiction vs. Non-Fiction)

Scan all shelf tags for Non-Fiction indicators:
- Tags `biography`, `gaming`, `non-fiction`, `writing-and-movie-making` → Non-Fiction
- Default → Fiction

IDs loaded dynamically from DB at script start.

